Analysis

Figure 1 |a Relationship between ADMET parameters and physicochemcial properties

library(readxl)
df <- read_excel("nrd3367-s4.xls", sheet = 2)
df <- data.frame(df)
names(df)
##  [1] "MOLREGNO"           "Mean_pXC50"         "Count_1nM_hits"    
##  [4] "Count_1uM_hits"     "Count_pIC50"        "Min_pXC50"         
##  [7] "Max_pXC50"          "StdDev_pXC50"       "ALOGP"             
## [10] "MW_FREEBASE"        "NUM_RO5_VIOLATIONS" "Molecular_Species" 
## [13] "ADMET_score"        "ADMET_Score_Bin"    "R05_Failure"       
## [16] "AlogP_Bin"          "MWT_Bin"            "nM_Bin"            
## [19] "uM_Bin"
library(ggplot2)
library(cowplot)
p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = MW_FREEBASE, y = ALOGP, colour = factor(ADMET_Score_Bin), 
                                                                shape = factor(ADMET_Score_Bin))) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.8) + theme(legend.position = "none") + xlab("Molecular mass") +
  ylab("AlogP")
p

Figure 1 |b Relationship between ADMET parameters and physicochemcial properties

library(scales)
ggplot(df, aes(x = as.factor(ADMET_Score_Bin))) +
  geom_bar(aes(y = (..count..)/sum(..count..))) +
  geom_text(aes(y = ((..count..)/sum(..count..)), label = scales::percent((..count..)/sum(..count..))), stat = "count", vjust = -0.25) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent) +
  labs(y = "Percent of dataset", x = "ADMET score")

Figure 2 | a Relationship between in vitro potency and physicochemical properties

library(ggplot2)
library(plyr)
new_df <- df[, c("Mean_pXC50", "MWT_Bin")]
r2 <- ddply(new_df, .(MWT_Bin), summarize, mean = mean(Mean_pXC50))
r2 <- data.frame(r2)
r2$MWT_Bin <- factor(r2$MWT_Bin, levels = r2$MWT_Bin[order(r2$mean)])
p2 <- ggplot(r2, aes(x = MWT_Bin, y = mean, group = 1)) +   stat_summary(fun.y = sum, geom = "line") +
  geom_point(color = "black", fill = "white", alpha = 0.2, size = 12) 
p2 + xlab("Molecular mass bin") + ylab("Mean pIC50")

Figure 2 | b Relationship between in vitro potency and physicochemical properties

## Figure 2b
library(plyr)
new_df <- df[, c("Mean_pXC50", "AlogP_Bin")]
r2 <- ddply(new_df, .(AlogP_Bin), summarize, mean = mean(Mean_pXC50))
r2 <- data.frame(r2)
r2$AlogP_Bin <- factor(r2$AlogP_Bin, levels = r2$AlogP_Bin[order(r2$mean)])
p2 <- ggplot(r2, aes(x = AlogP_Bin, y = mean, group = 1)) +  
  stat_summary(fun.y = sum, geom = "line") +
  geom_point(color = "black", fill = "white", alpha = 0.2, size = 12)
p2 + xlab("AlogP bin") + ylab("Mean pIC50")

Figure 3 | a Relationship between promiscuity and physicochemical properties

MWT <- df$MWT_Bin
library(ggplot2)
df_MWT <- data.frame(table(MWT))
df_MWT$MWT <- factor(df_MWT$MWT, levels = df_MWT$MWT[order(df_MWT$Freq)])

ggp <- ggplot(df_MWT, aes(x = MWT, y = Freq)) + theme_bw() 
# counts
ggp + geom_bar(fill="lightgreen", stat = "identity") + xlab("Molecular mass") + ylab("Frequency")

Figure 3 | b Relationship between promiscuity and physicochemical properties

AlogP <- df$AlogP_Bin
library(ggplot2)
df_AlogP <- data.frame(table(AlogP))
df_AlogP$AlogP <- factor(df_AlogP$AlogP, levels = df_AlogP$AlogP[order(df_AlogP$Freq)])
plot <- ggplot(df_AlogP, aes(x = AlogP, y = Freq)) + theme_bw()
plot + geom_bar(fill = "lightblue", stat = "identity") + xlab("AlogP") + ylab("Frequency")

library(ggplot2)
species <- df$Molecular_Species
df_species <- data.frame(table(species))
df_species$species <- factor(df_species$species, levels = df_species$species[order(df_species$Freq)])
p3 <- ggplot(df_species, aes(x = species, y = Freq)) + theme_bw()
p3 + geom_bar(fill = "cyan", stat = "identity") + xlab(" ") + ylab("Frequency")

Figure 5 | b Relationship between in vitro potency and does for oral drugs

pXC50 <- df$Mean_pXC50

qplot(pXC50, geom = "blank") + 
  
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), color = "black", fill = "lightblue") + 
  
   stat_density(geom = "line", aes(colour = "black")) + ylab("Number of Observations") +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
